						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, central shrine in the Daṇḍīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">M.K. Rājakēsarivarman (Sundarachōḷa) Year 5: 962 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription has been assigned to Sundarachōḷa. It records that Dēvakumāra Kramavittan of Teṉṉūr, one of the <hi rend="italic">āḷuṅgaṇattār</hi> of Vēḷichchēri in Kōṭṭūr-nāḍu (a sub-division) of Puliyūr-kōṭṭam made a gift of ninety sheep for burning a perpetual lamp to Tirutaṇḍīśvara-dēvar of the above village.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.</hi> Vol. III. No. 114. </p>						

						</summary>
